title: I AM Criterium: Battle of Nashville
Southeast Regional Series: Event #4 Tour Stop Knoxville Knoxville
Ride615 Hoover Ride for Hope Gran Fondo
description:
Our 2013 was an exciting event.  The routes were challenging and fun.  The weather PERFECT!  We had great crowd of different levels of riders.  Our police escorts and WEMA oversight made for a safe and memorable day.
Our rest stops were well stocked and our volunteers were the best!
Lunch was provided with the help of Mt. Juliets very own Bar-B-Cutie and Jets pizza.  No one went hungrey after a great day of riding.

For 2014 we are making the fondo an even better experience with; better routes, more people, more support, and more fun!
course: We will have a 7, 25, 50, 75, and 100 mile route available. All routes are WELL marked and will have police support.
registration: Online registration ends September 25, day of will be an extra 10 dollars

title: Calfkiller Ride To The Sky
description: Fall ride along the Calf Killer River.  Both the 22 mile and the 62 mile ride are designed to show the beauty of the Upper Cumberland region.
course:
62 & 22 mile routes start together and ride together for the first 10 miles.  The 22 mile route will be challenging but rewarding with beautiful scenery and well manned rest stops.  The 62 mile after splitting off from the 22 mile group will start their first climb of the day.  After this climb the route winds around the country side to the 2nd rest stop at Calfkiller Brewery.  After this stop riders will ride along the countryside through rolling back roads till they reach Calfkiller Hwy where the rollers get a little more challenging until you reach the second climb of the day.  This one is a long beautiful climb that will take you to the top and the edge of the Cumberland Plateau. From here it's all down hill...kind-of.  
Both rides will return to the starting point where we will have live music, BBQ and drinks.
registration: Registration is $40 for both rides until Oct. 1 then the price is $45 and day of on site is $50.  All riders will receive event bag, tshirt, after ride BBQ and beverages.
directions: From East or West Exit I-40 at exit 287 head north, turn right on Neal St. 2nd Traffic turn left and you have arrived.  From north or south on Hwy 111, take the Spring St. (Hwy 70) exit, go west.  Turn left on Neal St. and approx. 1/4 mile you will see Nashville State on your right, follow signs to parking.

title: Clarksville Cyclocross Challenge
description: Riverside Bicycle Shop presents the Clarksville Cyclocross Challenge at Rotary Park.
course: A fast 1.5 mile course over mixed terrain. The course is mostly over grass with short sections of gravel, pavement, groomed singletrack, and sand.
registration: Online registration through USA Cycling. Add $5 to register on the day of the event. One-day licenses $10. Race day registration and packet pick-up available on race day at 8:30 AM. You must register at least 15 minutes before any race you intend to enter. $20 pre-regisister for all categories except Juniors. Add $5 if registering on the day of the event. $10 for Juniors. Everyone can compete in an additional race for only $5 each race. All racers must present a valid racing license or authorization to ride form. Unlicensed riders will be required to purchase a one-day license or annual license and will be placed in the appropriate category. All riders will be required to complete and sign a standard athlete entry release form. One-day licenses available at registration for $10. Annual licenses available at registration for $60. All start times Central. Total payout will not exceed $499 per category per day.
notes: Race held under USAC Permit 2014 -3030. Race numbers will be issued when you register. Race is sanctioned by USA Cycling and all USA Cycling rules apply. Riders must wear a CPSC approved helmet. Entry fees include $3 for USA Cycling insurance coverage and $2 for TBRA surcharge. There will be no refunds. Race will be held regardless of weather conditions. Protest period is 15 minutes after the results are posted. Bar ends must be removed from mountain bikes. All bicycles must have a freewheel and two working brakes.
directions: 2308 Rotary Park Drive, Clarksville, TN 37043. Google correctly maps this address. There is very limited parking inside the park. There is also construction going on near the race course. The entire park IS NOT closed for the event, so  to allow others to continue to enjoy the park, please park vehicles at Wall Construction outside the gates of the park and walk or ride to the registration area.
